    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Replace it with `importlib` or whatever seems appropriate and modern.",
    "closed_at": "2022-07-04T19:47:18Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I was looking into the problem and pyximport uses more deprecated components - e.g. we are implementing find_module hook which is deprecated from 3.10 [1]. Since we still need do compatibility magic (`importlib` cannot be used in python 2.7), maybe it will be easier to total refactor of pyximport rather than trying to fit `importlib` to old way of importing. (We will keep old pyximport for 2.7 support)\r\n\r\n[1] https://docs.python.org/3/library/importlib.html#importlib.abc.Finder.find_module",
            "created_at": "2022-01-08T07:31:13Z",
